SIMPLE: roughhew
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roughhew
<hw>Rough"hew`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
hew coarsely, without smoothing; <as>as, to <ex>roughhew</ex>
timber</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give the first form or shape to; to form rudely;
to shape approximately and rudely; to roughcast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There's a divinity that shapes our ends,⟦br⟧
<qex>Roughhew</qex> them how we will.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roughhewer</ent>⟦br⟧
